byLineInfo.name: Visit the ATG by Wrangler Store

features: KEEP COOL. Sweat-wicking fabric helps pull moisture from your body so you can stay comfortable during outdoor activities.
UV PROTECTION. UPF 30 offers built-in UV protection from the sun's harmful rays. Perfect for hiking to your favorite fishing spot, or out on the water, this shirt is ready for anything.
MOVE WITH EASE. Articulated elbows help you move comfortable when you're stretching or throwing out a line. Solids come in a stretch fabric for extra range of motion.

MULTI-PURPOSE. A built in glasses cleaner at the hem allows you to clean glasses or shades on the go. Whether you're climbing through the forest or out on the boat, keep your specs clean no matter where you go.
UTILITY STORAGE. A secure zip Napoleon pocket and a drop in pocket with a hook-and-loop closure offer locked-down storage. A utility tool loop helps carry other outdoor necessities.
body.description: ALL TERRAIN GEAR: You’re ready to take on your next great adventure, which is why ATG x Wrangler brings you performance outdoor apparel that’s got you covered. Nature doesn’t hold back, which is why we’ve designed a full collection of tops, pants, shorts, outerwear and more with stretch, moisture-wicking fabric that helps block the sun with UPF protection and keep you dry for comfort that doesn’t quit. The line is packed with innovative outdoor tech features like sunglasses cleaner at the hem of all shirts, durable, reinforced pants with reinforced and lightweight, breathable fabrics. Whether you’re camping at your favorite site, hiking a new trail or even just exploring your own backyard, we’ve got the gear you need. Any destination. Any terrain. Anytime.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I bought this shirt for my husband and he really likes it! I do too. We've already bought another in a different color. It has a really flattering fit and looks good enough to wear any time, not just hiking. He wore it to Easter with the family and got compliments. The sleeves actually come to the right spot on his wrists and can be rolled up if he wants to. He usually has to roll up sleeves just to make them look right because they never reach his wrists.The shirt keeps him cool and but doesn't look boxy like a lot of other camping shirts. He hasn't experienced any humidity in it yet, but we're planning on taking it to Orlando for a WDW visit later this year. It definitely works well in the Rocky Mountains.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality shirt
reviews.reviewText: The reason why I bought the shirt, is that it will serve me on my hikink trips. But the shirt is so beautiful and comfortable, that I intend to use it for my trips abroad and to going out to events. A really beautiful shirt, well made and sewn. Perfect value for money

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good shirt but quality decreasing
reviews.reviewText: I have several shirts from the ATG line including a few long sleave and several short sleave versions. I really like these shirts because they are comfortable and can be worn casually or professionally. This is my second shirt of this model, one recently purchased and the other from a couple years ago. The quality of the recent purchase is a little disappointing. The fabric doesn't feel to the same level (doesn't have cotton like the other ATG shirts), the fit is a little off (tighter in the arms and pits), and for some reason the buttons are plastic instead metal like my other ATG shirts. Seems silly because buttons can't save more than a few pennies in cost. But, overall, the shirt is still good, but not to the level it should be.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good shirt for backpacking and hiking
reviews.reviewText: I got this shirt for backpacking to replace synthetic t-shirts I've typically worn. I've hiked about 150 miles in it so far and love the versatility of long sleeves and roll-up option, along with an ability to unbutton the front to increase ventilation. The shirt dries very quickly, typically within minutes of taking my pack off. I like that this shirt has more discrete chest pockets than other companies/models and the plaid style is more unique than standard solid print shirts. The build quality is decent, with some loose threads, but I think the shirt is great inexpensive option for anyone experimenting with your gear and wanting to try out a long-sleeve without breaking the bank! One feature to note is that the sleeve attachments leave the cuffed sleeve on your forearm, as opposed to above the elbow in other shirts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You want this shirt
reviews.reviewText: If you want a shirt that is comfortable to wear and move around in, you want this shirt.If you want a shirt that is great in warm weather, dries quickly, can be worn with either sleeves folded up or down, you want this shirt.If you want a shirt that looks appropriate everywhere from a forest to an office to a date night and family event, you want this shirt.If you want a shirt that is so flattering your wife can't get enough of looking at you and buys you one in every color, you want this shirt.Seriously, I (the wife) love this shirt and so does my husband. I can't think of any context where I wouldn't recommend this shirt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The quality of the shirt is excellent, and the fabric is very lightweight but still has some body. Will order another one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I Got What I Expected
reviews.reviewText: I am tall and have long chimpanzee-like arms. I needed a good hiking shirt with sleeves that actually make it to my wrists. This shirt fit as expected and has enough sleeve for me. I wore it on a hike and it was comfortable. I will buy this again.I am 6'4" and about 230lbs. I ordered the 2XL it is a little loose on me which is kind of what I wanted.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great shirt that needs extra buttons on cuffs
reviews.reviewText: I wear this shirt for outdoor work. Not anything that is rough on the shirt, but am outside in the hot sun for hours at a time. It's been great. Looks good, feels cool. Only complaint is just one button on each cuff, and the position of it was huge, leaving sleeve falling way over the hand. Had someone sew extra buttons on, but it seems kinda ridiculous to sell it that way. Regardless, I'll buy more of these.
